Champion]] (first Heavyweight Champion in UFC history), [[UFC 10]] [[List of UFC champions#UFC Tournaments|Tournament Champion]], [[UFC 11]] [[List of UFC champions#UFC Tournaments|Tournament Champion]] and [[Pride Grand Prix 2000 Finals]] [[Tournament]]       [[Champion]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Chuck Liddell cropped.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Chuck Liddell]]\n|July 11, 2009 (''[[UFC 100]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship|UFC Light Heavyweight Champion]] and four UFC Light Heavyweight Championship defenses.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Matt Hughes.png|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Matt Hughes (fighter)|Matt Hughes]]\n|May 29, 2010 (''[[UFC 114]]'')\n|{{small|Two-time [[UFC Welterweight Championship|UFC Welterweight Champion]] and seven UFC Welterweight Championship defenses.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Tito Ortiz - November 2014 (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Tito Ortiz]]\n|July 7, 2012 (''[[UFC 148]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship|UFC Light Heavyweight Champion]] and five UFC Light Heavyweight Championship defenses.}}\n|-\n|[[File:PatMiletich.png|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Pat Miletich]]\n|July 5, 2014 (''[[UFC 175]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Welterweight Championship|UFC Welterweight Champion]] (first Welterweight Champion in UFC history), four UFC Welterweight Championship defenses and [[List of UFC champions#tournament winners|UFC 16 Welterweight Tournament Winner]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Bas Rutten.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Bas Rutten]]\n|July 11, 2015 (''[[UFC 189]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Heavyweight Championship|UFC Heavyweight Champion]], one-time [[List of Pancrase champions|Pancrase Openweight Champion]], and two Pancrase Openweight Championship defenses.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Antonio Rodrigo Nogueira \"Minotauro\" Paris - 2004.JPG|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Ant\u00f4nio Rodrigo Nogueira]]\n|July 10, 2016 (''UFC Fan Expo'')\n|{{small|One-time [[List of PRIDE champions#Heavyweight Championship|Pride Heavyweight Champion]], one-time [[List of PRIDE champions#Heavyweight Championship|Interim Pride Heavyweight Champion]] and one-time [[UFC Heavyweight Championship|Interim UFC Heavyweight Champion]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Don Frye 1996 ufc10.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Don Frye]]\n|July 10, 2016 (''UFC Fan Expo'')\n|{{small|[[List of UFC Champions#UFC Tournaments|UFC 8 Tournament Winner]], [[List of UFC Champions#UFC Tournaments|UFC 10 Tournament Finalist]]  and [[List of UFC Champions#UFC Tournaments|UFC Ultimate Ultimate 1996 Tournament Winner]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Maurice Smith 1999.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Maurice Smith (kickboxer)|Maurice Smith]]\n|July 6, 2017 (''UFC Fan Expo'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Heavyweight Championship|UFC Heavyweight Champion]], one UFC Heavyweight Championship defense, one-time [[Battlecade Extreme Fighting#Heavyweight Championship|Extreme Fighting Heavyweight Championship]] and one Extreme Fighting Heavyweight Championship defense.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Kazushi Sakuraba 2015.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Kazushi Sakuraba]]\n|July 6, 2017 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2017'')\n|{{small|[[List of UFC champions|UFC Japan Heavyweight Tournament Winner]], most submission wins in [[Pride FC]] history, competed in longest fight in [[Pride FC]] history, and first fighter to defeat [[Royce Gracie]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Matt Serra 2007.png|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Matt Serra]]\n|July 5, 2018 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2018'')\n|{{small|One-time [[List of UFC champions|UFC Welterweight Champion]], [[The Ultimate Fighter 4|The Ultimate Fighter 4 Welterweight Tournament Winner]] and first fighter to win both a [[List of UFC Champions#The Ultimate Fighter|''The Ultimate Fighter'' Tournament]] and [[List of UFC Champions|UFC Championship]]}}\n|-\n|[[File:RichFranklinphoto.png|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Rich Franklin]]\n|July 5, 2019 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2019'')\n|{{small|One-time [[List of UFC champions|UFC Middleweight Champion]], two UFC Middleweight Championship defenses.}}\n|}\n\n===Modern-era wing===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|+\n|-\n! style=\"width:7%;\" |\n! style=\"width:10%;\" |Name\n! style=\"width:10%;\" |Date of Induction<br>(event)\n! class=\"unsortable\" | '''UFC recognized accolades'''\n|-\n|[[File:Forrest Griffin - UFC 100 Fan Expo - Mandalay Bay Casino, Las Vegas.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Forrest Griffin]]\n|July 6, 2013 (''[[UFC 162]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship|UFC Light Heavyweight Champion]] and [[The Ultimate Fighter 1|The Ultimate Fighter 1: Light Heavyweight Tournament Winner]].}}\n\n|-\n|[[File:US Army 51883 Ultimate Fighting Champion motivates wounded warriors cropped.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[B.J. Penn]]\n|July 11, 2015 (''[[UFC 189]]'')\n|{{small|One-time [[UFC Welterweight Championship|UFC Welterweight Champion]], one-time [[UFC Lightweight Championship|UFC Lightweight Champion]] with three UFC Lightweight Championship defenses, and [[List of UFC champions#Tournament Winners|UFC 41 Lightweight Tournament Co-Champion]].}}\n|-\n|[[File:Urijah Faber 24 July 2009.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Urijah Faber]]\n|July 6, 2017 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2017'')\n|{{small|One-time [[WEC Featherweight Championship|WEC Featherweight Champion]] with five WEC Featherweight Championship defenses. First [[Bantamweight (MMA)|bantamweight]] inductee.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Ronda Rousey.jpeg|186x186px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Ronda Rousey]]\n|July 5, 2018 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2018'')\n|{{small|First [[List_of_UFC_champions#Women's_championship_history|Women's UFC Champion]], UFC Bantamweight Champion from 2012-2015 with 6 defenses. First female inductee, second bantamweight inductee.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Michael Bisping.jpg|100px]]\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Michael Bisping]]\n|July 5, 2019 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2019'')\n|{{small|One-Time [[UFC Middleweight Championship|UFC Middleweight Champion]] with one UFC Middleweight Championship defense, [[The Ultimate Fighter 3]] Light Heavyweight winner, first inductee from [[England]]}}\n|-\n|[[File:RashadEvans.png|alt=|left|104x104px]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Rashad Evans]]\n|July 5, 2019 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2019'')\n|{{Small|One-time [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship|UFC Light Heavyweight Champion]] and [[The Ultimate Fighter 2]] Heavyweight Winner.}}\n|}\n<br />\n\n===Contributors===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:7%;\"|\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Date of Induction<br>(event)\n! class=\"unsortable\"| '''Contributions'''\n|-\n|[[File:TPAR2009.jpg|100px]]\n|[[Charles Lewis Jr.]]<br>(Mask)\n|July 11, 2009 (''[[UFC 100]]'')\n|{{small|Founded the first major mixed martial arts clothing line [[Tapout (clothing brand)|Tapout]].}}\n|-\n|\n|[[Jeff Blatnick]]\n|July 11, 2015 (''[[UFC 189]]'')\n|{{small|Commentator, UFC commissioner and was instrumental in helping the UFC get regulated by athletic commissions.}}\n|-\n|\n|[[Bob Meyrowitz]]\n|July 10, 2016 (''UFC Fan Expo'')\n|{{small|UFC co-creator and owner from UFC 6 to until it was sold to Zuffa in January 2001.}}\n|-\n|\n|[[Joe Silva]]\n|July 6, 2017 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2017'')\n|{{small|UFC matchmaker from 1997 to 2016.}}\n|-\n|\n|[[Bruce Connal]]\n|July 5, 2018 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2018'')\n|{{small|UFC television producer from 1997-2018.}}\n|-\n|[[File:Art Davie - photo credit Art Davie.jpg|100px]]\n|[[Art Davie]]\n|July 5, 2018 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony, 2018'')\n|{{small|UFC co-creator, co-owner from UFC 1 to UFC 5 and first UFC matchmaker.}}\n|}\n\n===Fights===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Fight\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Date of Induction<br>(event)\n! class=\"unsortable\"| '''Notes'''\n|-\n|[[Forrest Griffin]] [[Forrest Griffin vs. Stephan Bonnar|vs]]. [[Stephan Bonnar]] I\n|July 6, 2013\n|{{small|Regarded as the one of the greatest fights in UFC history. Marked a turning point for the UFC in terms of its journey to mainstream acceptance of MMA as a popular, legitimate sport. Forrest Griffin def. Stephan Bonnar by unanimous decision at ''[[The Ultimate Fighter 1 Finale]]''.}}\n|-\n|[[Matt Hughes (fighter)|Matt Hughes]] [[UFC 52|vs]]. [[Frank Trigg]] II\n|July 11, 2015\n|{{small|For the [[List of UFC champions#Welterweight Championship|UFC Welterweight Championship]]. Matt Hughes def. Frank Trigg by submission in Round 1 at ''[[UFC 52]]''.}}\n|-\n|[[Mark Coleman]] [[UFC 17|vs]]. [[Pete Williams (fighter)|Pete Williams]]\n|July 10, 2016\n|{{small|Pete Williams def. Mark Coleman by head-kick KO, the second head-kick KO in UFC history after Gordeau vs Tuli (''[[UFC 1]]'') at ''[[UFC 17]]''. One of the biggest upsets in early UFC history.}}\n|-\n|[[Maur\u00edcio Rua]] [[UFC 139|vs]]. [[Dan Henderson]] I<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ufc.com/news/The-Fight-Henderson-vs-Shogun-I|title=The Fight - Henderson vs. Shogun I|work=UFC|access-date=2018-05-14|language=en}}</ref>\n|July 5, 2018 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony'')\n|{{small|Dan Henderson def. Maur\u00edcio Rua by unanimous decision in a back-and-forth fight at ''[[UFC 139]]''.  Second five-round non-title fight in UFC history and first to go the distance.}}\n|-\n|[[Diego Sanchez]] [[The Ultimate Fighter: United States vs. United Kingdom Finale|vs]]. [[Clay Guida]]\n|July 5, 2019 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony'')\n|{{small|Diego Sanchez def. Clay Guida by split decision in a three round, back-and-forth fight in the lightweight division at ''[[The Ultimate Fighter: United States vs. United Kingdom Finale]]''.}}\n|-\n|[[Jon Jones]] [[UFC 165|vs]]. [[Alexander Gustafsson]]\n|July 9,2020 (''UFC Hall of Fame Ceremony'')\n|{{small|Jon Jones def. Alexander Gustafsson by unanimous decision in closely fought five-round fight for the [[UFC Light Heavyweight Championship]] at ''[[UFC 165]]''. Fight of the Night.}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Ex