{"title_page": "1909 Victorian soccer season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition = [[Football Victoria]]\n  | season      = 1909\n  | winners     = \n  | prevseason  = \n  | nextseason  = [[1910 Victorian soccer season|1910]]\n}}\n\nThe 1909 Victorian soccer season was the first competitive season of [[Association football|soccer]] in the [[Australia|Australian]] state of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], under association with the governing body of [[Football Victoria]]. The season consisted of one league made up of six 'district' teams from [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]] that was known as the 'Amateur League'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ozfootball.net/ark/States/VIC/1909Overview.html|title=Victorian Season - 1909 Overview|website=www.ozfootball.net}}</ref> This league season is recognized as being the first season of first tier Victorian state soccer that is now formally recognized as the [[National Premier Leagues Victoria]], in which [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]] were crowned as the inaugural premiers. The calendar season also saw the commencement of the [[Dockerty Cup]], in which [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]] defeated [[St Kilda SC (1909\u20131934)|St Kilda]] 2\u20131,<ref>http://www.ozfootball.net/ark/States/VIC/Cup.html</ref> making United first club in the state's history to achieve both respective accolades in the same season.\n\n==League Tables==\n===Victorian Amateur League===\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[National Premier Leagues Victoria|Victorian Amateur League]]\n| season             = 1909\n| winners            = [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]]\n| relegated          = \n| league topscorer   = \n| biggest home win   = [[St Kilda SC (1909\u20131934)|St Kilda]] 10\u20130 [[Yarraville FC|Williamstown]]<br /><small>(12 June 1909)</small>\n| biggest away win   = [[Fitzroy District FC|Fitzroy]] 0\u20139 [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]]<br /><small>(17 July 1909)</small>\n| highest scoring    = [[Melbourne United FC|Melbourne United]] 2\u20139 [[Yarraville FC|Williamstown]]<br /><small>(22 May 1909)</small>\n| matches            = 30\n| total goals        = 150\n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         =\n| nextseason         = [[1910 Victorian soccer season|1910]]\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2|drawpoints=1|losspoints=0\n\n|team1=CU|name_CU=[[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]]\n|team2=SK|name_SK=[[St Kilda SC (1908\u20131934)|St Kilda]]\n|team3=MU|name_MU=[[Melbourne United FC|Melbourne United]]\n|team4=WS|name_WS=[[Yarraville FC|Williamstown]]\n|team5=FD|name_FD=[[Fitzroy District FC|Fitzroy]]\n|team6=PR|name_PR=[[Brighton SC|Prahran]]\n\n|win_CU=9|draw_CU=1|loss_CU=0|gf_CU=40|ga_CU=4|status_ES=C\n|win_MU=4|draw_MU=0|loss_MU=6|gf_MU=23|ga_MU=34\n|win_FD=3|draw_FD=1|loss_FD=6|gf_FD=14|ga_FD=34\n|win_SK=7|draw_SK=0|loss_SK=3|gf_SK=40|ga_SK=17\n|win_WS=3|draw_WS=1|loss_WS=6|gf_WS=22|ga_WS=32\n|win_PR=2|draw_PR=1|loss_PR=7|gf_PR=11|ga_PR=29\n\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source=<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ozfootball.net/ark/States/VIC/1909ALT.html|title=Victorian Amateur League - 1909 Season Table|website=www.ozfootball.net}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{National Premier Leagues}}\n{{AUS fb general}}\n{{AUS fb states sm}}\n{{AUS fb state Vic}}\n\n[[Category:1909 in Australian soccer|Football Federation Victoria]]\n[[Category:Soccer in Victoria (Australia)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n  | competition = [[Football Victoria]]\n  | season      = 1909\n  | winners     = \n  | prevseason  = \n  | nextseason  = [[1910 Football Victoria season|1910]]\n}}\n\nThe 1909 Victorian soccer season was the first competitive season of [[Association football|soccer]] in the [[Australia|Australian]] state of [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], under association with the governing body of [[Football Victoria]]. The season consisted of one league made up of six 'district' teams from [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]] that was known as the 'Amateur League'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ozfootball.net/ark/States/VIC/1909Overview.html|title=Victorian Season - 1909 Overview|website=www.ozfootball.net}}</ref> This league season is recognized as being the first season of first tier Victorian state soccer that is now formally recognized as the [[National Premier Leagues Victoria]], in which [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]] were crowned as the inaugural premiers. The calendar season also saw the commencement of the [[Dockerty Cup]], in which [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]] defeated [[St Kilda SC (1909\u20131934)|St Kilda]] 2\u20131,<ref>http://www.ozfootball.net/ark/States/VIC/Cup.html</ref> making United first club in the state's history to achieve both respective accolades in the same season.\n\n==League Tables==\n===Victorian Amateur League===\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[National Premier Leagues Victoria|Victorian Amateur League]]\n| season             = 1909\n| winners            = [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]]\n| relegated          = \n| league topscorer   = \n| biggest home win   = [[St Kilda SC (1909\u20131934)|St Kilda]] 10\u20130 [[Yarraville FC|Williamstown]]<br /><small>(12 June 1909)</small>\n| biggest away win   = [[Fitzroy District FC|Fitzroy]] 0\u20139 [[Carlton United FC|Carlton United]]<br /><small>(17 July 1909)</small>\n| highest scoring    = [[Melbourne United FC|Melbourne United]] 2\u20139 [[Yarraville FC|Williamstown]]<br /><small>(22 May 1909)</small>\n| matches            = 30\n| total goals        = 150\n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         =\n| nextseason         = [[1910 Victorian Football season|1910]]\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2|drawpo