016810|oclc=18068942|accessdate=2017-10-07|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Cerami|first=Charles A.|year=2002|url=https://archive.org/details/banneker00char/page/n5/mode/1up|title=Benjamin Banneker: Surveyor, Astronomer, Publisher, Patriot|place=New York|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=0585423946|lccn=2001046960|oclc=50739343|accessdate=2019-09-19|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n**{{cite web|last=Corrigan|first=Mary Beth|date=April 2003|title=Benjamin Banneker: Fabled Genius Considered\": Review of Cerami, Charles A. (2002), ''Benjamin Banneker: Surveyor, Astronomer, Publisher, Patriot'', New York: John Wiley & Sons ''\"H-Net Reviews in the Humanities & Social Sciences:  H-Net Maryland''|url=http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=7440|work=H-Net: Humanities & Social Sciences Online|location=[[Lansing, Michigan]]|publisher=MATRIX: The Center for Humane Arts, Letters and Social Sciences Online: Department of History: [[Michigan State University]]|accessdate=2013-07-08|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905204059/http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=7440|archivedate=2012-09-05}} \n* {{cite book|last=Crew|first=Harvey W.|last2=Webb|first2=William Bensing|last3=Wooldridge|first3=John|year=1892|url=https://books.google.com/?id=5Q81AAAAIAAJ&&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q&f=false|work=Centennial History of the City of Washington, D.C.|publisher=United Brethren Publishing House|location=[[Dayton, Ohio]]|title=IV. \"Permanent Capital Site Selected\"|page=87|lccn=06028029|oclc=2843595|accessdate=2009-05-07|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Glawe|first=Eddie|url=http://www.xyht.com/professional-surveyor-archives/feature-benjamin-banneker/|title=Feature: Benjamin Banneker|work=Professional Surveyor Magazine|date=2014-02-13|volume=39|issue=6|publisher=Flatdog Media, Inc.|accessdate=2018-02-18|via=[http://www.xyht.com xyHt]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130044246/http://www.xyht.com/professional-surveyor-archives/feature-benjamin-banneker/|archivedate=2017-01-30}} \n* {{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Richard|url=http://www.blackpast.org/aah/banneker-benjamin-1731-1806|title=Banneker, Benjamin (1731-1806)|work=Online Encyclopedia of Significant People and Places in African American History|year=2007|publisher=BlackPast.org|accessdate=2016-06-03|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409121622/http://www.blackpast.org/aah/banneker-benjamin-1731-1806|archivedate=2016-04-09|df=}}\n* {{cite book|last=Jusserand|first=Jean Jules|author-link=Jean Jules Jusserand|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u2MUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA137#v=onepage&q&f=false|work=With Americans of Past and Present Days|lccn=16011605|oclc=1075914|title=Major L'Enfant and the Federal City|location=New York|publisher=Charles Scribner's Sons|pages=137\u2013195|year=1916|accessdate=2011-08-15|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Sidney|last1=Kaplan|first2=Emma Nogrady|last2=Kaplan|year=1989|url=https://archive.org/details/blackpresenceint00kap_ktt/page/132/mode/2up/search/Banneker|title=Benjamin Banneker|work=The Black Presence in the Era of the American Revolution|chapter=V. The Emergence of Gifts and Powers|edition=revised|location=[[Amherst, Massachusetts]]|publisher=[[University of Massachusetts Press]]|pages=132\u2013151|lccn=88022111|oclc=43475547|isbn=0870236628|accessdate=February 29, 2020|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Latrobe|first=John H. B., Esq.|url=https://archive.org/details/memoirbenjaminb00socigoog/page/n7/mode/1up|title=Memoir of Benjamin Banneker: Read before the Maryland Historical Society at the Monthly Meeting, May 1, 1845|location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed by John D. Toy|year=1845|lccn=rc01003345|oclc=85791076|accessdate=February 29, 2020|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Linklater|first=Andro|title=The fabric of America: how our borders and boundaries shaped the country and forged our national identity|location=New York|publisher=Walker & Co.|isbn=0-8027-1533-8|oclc=138533044|year=2007|url=https://books.google.com/?id=08d1AAAAMAAJ|accessdate=2017-10-07|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/selectionsfromle00maso#page/n9/mode/2up|title=Selections from the letters and manuscripts of the late Susanna Mason; with a brief memoir of her life, by her daughter|last=Mason|first=Rachel|year=1836|location=Philadelphia|publisher=Rackliff & Jones, Printers, S.W. corner of George & Swanwick Streets|lccn=unk83001993|oclc=786297945|accessdate=2018-03-01|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite thesis |last=Perot|first=Sandra W. |date=February 2014 |title=Reconstructing Molly Welsh: Race, Memory and the Story of Benjamin Banneker's Grandmother|type=M.A.|location=[[Amherst, Massachusetts]]|publisher=[[University of Massachusetts Amherst]] |work=Masters Theses 1911-February 2014: Paper 210: ScholarWorks@UMass Amherst|oclc=314413559}}\n:*[http://scholarworks.umass.edu/theses/210/ Introduction and abstract.] Retrieved 2015-11-15. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929100518/http://scholarworks.umass.edu/theses/210/|date=September 29, 2015}}\n:*[http://scholarworks.umass.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1215&context=theses Full text] Retrieved March 1, 2018.  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001211829/http://scholarworks.umass.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1215&context=theses|date=October 1, 2015}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Phillips|first=P. Lee|year=1917|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LSkkCeq5R1AC&pg=PA114#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Negro, Benjamin Banneker; Astronomer and Mathematician, Plea for Universal Peace (Read before the Society, April 18, 1916)|work=Records of the Columbia Historical Society|publisher=Columbia Historical Society, Washington, D.C.|volume=20|pages=114\u2013120|issn=0897-9049|lccn=18019397|oclc=1564221|accessdate=2009-04-15|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Stewart|first=John|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GgULOzNSafMC&pg=PA48#v=o